Destiny and I took a trip all the way up to Montana this past weekend to compete at IWPA Weight Pull Nationals. At 3 months shy of 11 years old my old girl still out there putting it down. On Saturday she took 1st place and Most Weight Pulled Per Pound overall on Snow and broke the 19 year old IWPA World Record with a 6 second pull. Then turned around on Sunday and took another 1st place and Most Weight Pulled Per Pound light weight division on wheels. She also won 3 Regional Good Medals over the season. She gave me her all and left it all out there. As always Super Proud of her performance!

Here are a few pictures from IWPA National Championships on snow and wheels. I had the good fortune to pull 3 dogs that all had successful weekends. Aidew became a 2X National Champion on wheels and on snow. Amara became a 4X National Champion on wheels and a 2x National Champion on snow and Jenna Star’s dog Dezzy became a National Champion on snow and a 2x National Champion on wheels.  ALL of the dogs worked extremely hard for me on both days. Results over excuses! Happy Heavenly Birthday Punisher!!

Aidew made me proud this past weekend at the Houston World Series of Dog Shows. In four days in a row of showing on a huge stage, complete with any distraction that you can imagine, he earned his Companion Dog Excellent (CDX) Open Obedience title. He really held it together day in and day out while we watched some very good teams fold or pull their entries at the end. Ironically, he had his best performance and earned his highest score on the fourth day. On to Utility! Results over excuses.
